cs.CC, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the analysis of a game played by two players, which involves probability distributions and predicates. This suggests that the paper may belong to the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) or information theory (cs.IT). The use of parallel repetition and the study of the case where the players are not restricted to local computations suggest that the paper may also belong to the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and game theory (cs.GT), respectively. Finally, the mention of Raz's proof suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
